Lakers, Spurs Win to Tie NBA Playoff Series 1-1; Thunder Lead Nuggets 2-0

-- B y   N a n c y   K e r c h e v a l
-- 
2011-04-21T06:33:27Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-21/lakers-spurs-win-to-tie-nba-playoff-series-1-1-thunder-lead-nuggets-2-0.html
The defending champion  Los Angeles 
Lakers and  San Antonio Spurs  rebounded from opening-game home
losses to tie their National Basketball Association playoff
series at one game apiece.  The Lakers beat the New Orleans Hornets 87-78 and the Spurs
won 93-87 against the Memphis Grizzlies. Also last night, the
Oklahoma City Thunder beat the Denver Nuggets 106-89 to lead
their Western Conference series two games to none.  Andrew Bynum had 17 points and 11 rebounds, while Lamar Odom came off the bench to score 16 for the Lakers at the
Staples Center in Los Angeles. Trevor Ariza tallied 22 points
and Chris Paul added 20 for the Hornets, who host the Lakers
tomorrow in Game 3.  At AT&T Center in San Antonio,  Manu Ginobili  had 17 points,
while  Tim Duncan , Richard Jefferson and George Hill each had 16
points for the Spurs. Sam Young had 17 and Tony Allen scored 15
for the Grizzlies, who host Game 3 on April 23.  At Oklahoma City Arena,  Kevin Durant  scored 23 points and
Russell Westbrook added 21 for the Thunder, who now travel to
Denver for Game 3, also on April 23.  Tonight, the Chicago Bulls are looking for their third
straight win at the Indiana Pacers; the Miami Heat will seek to
take a 3-0 lead at the Philadelphia 76ers, and the Portland
Trail Blazers will chase their first victory against the
visiting Dallas Mavericks, who have two wins.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nancy Kercheval in Washington at 
